experienceEntries.description:
Project Manager
Led a variety of projects including launching new services, large-scale infrastructure programs, systems integration, process reengineering, and deployments. Responsible for the planning and execution from start (developing the business case) to finish (project close-out) of Projects. Manage project scope, schedule, budget, quality, risks and issues, impact on systems, and dependencies to other IT Business
Units within the organization. Ability to quickly earn the trust of sponsors and key stakeholders; mobilize and motivate teams; set direction and approach; resolved conflict; deliver tough messages with grace; execute with limited information and ambiguity. Ability to communicate at all levels with clarity and precision both written and verbally formats. Maintain extensive knowledge and expertise in the use of
project management and SDLC methodologies and tools. Able to navigate through a large corporate environment to ensure appropriate processes are met. Maintain excellent problem-solving and criticalthinking skills. Able to demonstrate, applied experience establishing and delivering complex projects.
The project budget was $5Billion.
 - Managed single accountable for defining, planning, orchestrating, and delivering a given initiative.
 - Ensured end results are of the highest caliber with a clearly articulated scope and quantifiable business (i.e. financial) benefit.
 - Use Earned Value Management (EVM) and Critical Path Method (CPM) to ensure integrity and delivery of multiple projects with respect to time, budget, scope, change, risk and resources.
 - Managed with implementation of COTS applications, enterprise tools, and infrastructure projects.
 - Direct large-scale, complex projects often involving multiple internal and external constituents and matrixed partners.
 - Developed for one or more initiatives including business, operational, and IT deliverables.
 - Directly manages all aspects of the project lifecycle and work with matrixed IT infrastructure partners to oversee all SDLC phases or iterations of an Agile project.
 - Rigorously managed scope to ensure commitments are achieved within agreed on time, cost, and quality parameters.
 - Validated financial forecast and provide on-going reconciliation of resources and other related project expenditures.
 - Developed communication plan and effectively communicates in both verbal (e.g. day-to-day discussions, team meetings) and written (status reports, change requests) form.
 - Served as a subject matter expert in routinely briefing key stakeholders on different aspects of assigned initiatives.
 - Ensured that sound practices are taking place. Replace old processes with newer ones where feasible, and provides feedback for efficiencies.
 - Represented the project in various project governance and inter-department forums.
 - Developed the project charter, integrated project plan, resource plan, contingency plan, and related project management artifacts.
 - Managed, define and track project milestones while developing, maintaining, and reporting on an overall integrated delivery plan.
 - Managed and accurately assess risks and issues.
 - Maintained current statements of work for all contractors; track and approve contractor invoices in a timely manner.
 - Provided regular updates to program C-level executive director, project sponsor and stakeholders on the status of the budget and document reasons for budget excess or shortfall.
 - Published periodic project status reports.
 - Proposed recommendations and adjustments.
 - Performed additional job-related duties as requested to get the job done

Advanced planning, organization, analytics and business acumen are required to understand and present the implications of various decisions. Manage the delivery efforts of Managers and Directors, provide leadership, and influence for VP levels and above in the selection and governance of IT Initiatives.

Manage the assignment, development and performance of Project Managers under the program.

Compliance Processes. Functioning of an IT governance PMO office, interacting with executive steering committees and business stakeholders at varying levels.

Communication skills are required to persuade, gain cooperation, provide formal presentations to various sized groups and to reach consensus and resolve conflict.

(specifically using Artemis)
